owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

stake(uint256,address).details: Stake `amount` of assets to this contract

params.amount: The amount of assets to be staked
params.onBehalfOf: The address that will receive the staked position, same as msg.sender if the user   wants to receive them on his own wallet.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.amount: The amount of assets to withdraw
params.to: The address that will receive the staked assets, same as msg.sender if the user   wants to receive them on his own wallet.

withdrawByLendingPool(uint256,address,ad.details: Withdraw `amount` of staked assets called by lendingPool only lendingPool can call this function in `unstakeAndWithdraw()` of LendingPool

params.amount: The amount of assets to withdraw
params.to: The address that will receive the staked assets, same as msg.sender if the user   wants to receive them on his own wallet.
params.user: The user of the staked position

constructor.notice: This contract must be create in lendingPool's `initReserve()`
